2. LEITH.

The stream that bears thy name brings no end of boons, and in thy rich bosom are weicomed a thousand barks. By topgailant and keel thy pilots outvie the Dutch, and far Ceylon and Thule know thy sails, and so do the waters of the East and West. 2. LETHA.

Mille bonis te, Letha, beat cognominis unda, Excipis et gremio divite mille rates. Tu regis antennas, et puppibus aequora sulcas,

Et Batavum certas antevolare trabes. Lintea Taprobane tua novit, et ultima Thule, Quidquid et undarum vesper et ortus habet. Tu Solis Lunaeque vias et sidera calles, Et numeras gemini signa corusca poli. Fluctibus in mediis quoties tu carbasa pandis, Imperio parent ventus et unda tuo. Nobilis urbs, aut te docuit surgente procella,

Aut a te didicit findere Tiphys aquas.
